----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This examples creates a homogeneous halfspace with a refined area in the middle of the model.
It will be a single volume block with a constant elastic material property, using CUBIT. 


0. (optional) re-create mesh:
     run CUBIT/Trelis:
     > claro (or cubit)

     then run meshing script:
     claro -> Menu "Tools" -> "Play Journal File" ... and select file: "block_mesh.py"

     if everything goes fine, this creates the mesh files in subdirectory MESH/:
        MESH/absorbing_surface_file_bottom
        MESH/absorbing_surface_file_xmax
        MESH/absorbing_surface_file_xmin
        MESH/absorbing_surface_file_ymax
        MESH/absorbing_surface_file_ymin
        MESH/free_or_absorbing_surface_file_zmax
        MESH/materials_file
        MESH/mesh_file
        MESH/nodes_coords_file
        MESH/nummaterial_velocity_file

     the cubit graphics window should show a mesh similar to the file homogeneous.png

1. run the simulation, type:
  > ./run_this_example

  and compare the files in OUTPUT_FILES/ with the reference solution in REF_SEIS/


